meaning:
fundamental cognitive orientation of an individual or society encompassing the whole of the individual's or society's knowledge, culture, and point of view.;
can include natural philosophy, fundamental, existential, and normative postulates, or themes, values, emotions, and ethic;
the result of arranging perceptions into existing imagery by imagination[Piaget];

The act of presevration and recording of individual or cultural ideas, thoughts, beliefs, 
narratives with a medium of language using a sets of meanings, terms, concepts;
The result of writing what has said or thought or imagined at a period of time and some locations;
